g.text: - Usually crawls a list of URLs once.
- Is focused on initial discovery, link extraction, or basic data collection.
- Does not handle frequent updates or detect changes to previously seen pages.
We do not need a sophisticated URLFrontier that manages:
so we use a simple FIFO Queue (BFS traversal)
and we use a threshold value for the URLs that traversed the URLFrontier
(Number of URLs that traversed the Queue)
and stop the program when we exceed that threshold value
